from Valdez, Alaska, on Prince William Sound, to West Coast and other refineries.
The first comm ercial tanker carrying Alaskan North Slope oil left Valdez, Alaska, for the West Coast on August 1, 1977.
The first commercial tanker exporting such oil left Valdez for Asia on May 31, 1996, approximately 6 months after the legislation lifting the ban was enacted.1 (See fig. 1.)
