The oil industry is exploring ways to convert the natural gas to liquid to be transported of f the North Slope, possibly through traditional pipelines such as the Trans-Alaska Pipeline.
BP and Amoco merged in 1998.
In April 1999, BP-Amoco and ARCO confirmed plans to merge.
